THE CITY IS THE BEST CANDIDATE FOR THIS GRANT, DUE TO ITS DISTINCTIVENESS TO OTHER CITIES IN PENNSYLVANIA, IN WHICH THE MINORITY POPULATION IS THE MAJORITY. 54% OF RESIDENTS IDENTIFY AS HISPANIC, 14% AFRICAN AMERICAN, 3% ASIAN AND 11% AS TWO OR MORE RACES.

"15.DESCRIPTION OF PROJECT

THE NORTH CENTRAL PENNSYLVANIA REGIONAL PLANNING AND DEVELOPMENT COMMISSION INTENDS TO DEVELOP A COMPREHENSIVE REGIONAL CORRIDOR SAFETY ACTION PLAN DESIGNED TO SIGNIFICANTLY REDUCE TRAFFIC FATALITIES AND SERIOUS INJURIES ON THE REGION?S PUBLIC ROADWAYS AND TO PROVIDE A FOCUSED EVALUATION OF SAFETY RELATED ISSUES THAT PROVIDE KEY TRANSPORTATION LINKS TO CRITICAL ECONOMIC CENTERS AND RECREATIONAL ASSETS.  IT WILL ANALYZE REGIONAL SAFETY CONCERNS BY EXAMINING EXISTING AND HISTORICAL DATA, ROADWAY CHARACTERISTICS, INPUT FROM REGIONAL STAKEHOLDERS, AND PUBLIC CONCERNS WHILE IDENTIFYING A COMPREHENSIVE SET OF STRATEGIES FOR FUTURE IMPLEMENTATION.
